Lambda at edge and CloudFront functions.

Both run code at CloudFront edge locations, closer to users than your origin region, but they differ sharply in power and cost.

Lambda at edge runs Node or Python, can run for several seconds, and crucially can make network calls to other services, so it's for things like authentication, a-b routing, and header rewrites that need a lookup. CloudFront functions run only JavaScript, must finish in well under a millisecond, and have no network access at all, so they're for pure header and url transforms and simple redirects.

The rule: reach for CloudFront functions, the cheaper and faster default, for lightweight header and url work, and reach for Lambda at edge when the logic needs a network call or a richer runtime.
